title: PPPP’s Sohail Anwar wins PS-12 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) Sohail Anwar has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-12 Larkana-III by securing 54,077 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Moazzam Ali Khan of the Grand Democratic Alliance who bagged 31,850 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 46.96%.
